{"word":"κατερείπω","slug":"κατερείπω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κατερείπω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ψω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to throw</i> or <i>cast down</i>, Orac. <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to fall in ruins</i>, of Troy, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> in aor2 <el>κατ-ήρῐπον</el>, <i>to fall down, fall prostrate</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a>, <el>τεῖχος κατ-ερήριπεν</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}